cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.PF, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with WLAN stations and their association rates with an Access Point. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the modeling of simultaneous TCP-controlled transfers using a Markov Chain. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper focuses on computing aggregate download throughput numerically. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses a procedure to compute aggregate download throughput using a Markov Chain model. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely as the paper does not explicitly discuss security or cryptography, but it may be relevant if the paper discusses any security implications of the simultaneous transfers.
